The '''Craiova II Power Station''' is a large [[thermal power plant]] located in [[Craiova]], [[Romania]], having 2 generation groups of 150 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] each having a total [[electricity]] generation capacity of 300 MW.<ref>[http://www.energie-gratis.ro/termocentrale.php Cele mai mari termocentrale din Romania {{ro}}] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004192737/http://www.energie-gratis.ro/termocentrale.php |date=2011-10-04 }}</ref>

There are plans to add another generating group of 150 [[Megawatt|MW]] at '''Craiova II Power Station''' that will result a total power generating capacity of 450 [[MWh]]<ref>[http://www.gds.ro/Economie/2008-12-01/CE+Craiova+vrea+o+noua+termocentrala CE Craiova vrea o noua termocentrala]</ref> at a cost of US$225 million.

