[[File:International Institute of Tropical Forestry.JPG|thumb|The International Institute of Tropical Forestry c. 1960]]

The '''International Institute of Tropical Forestry''' is a program of the [[United States Forest Service]] that was founded in 1939.  It is headquartered in [[Rio Piedras]], [[Puerto Rico]], on the grounds of the [[University of Puerto Rico]]'s Agricultural Experimental Station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fs.usda.gov/main/iitf/about |title=About the Institute |publisher=Fs.fed.us |date= |accessdate=2014-05-18}}</ref> Events on May 20, 2014 mark the Institute's 75th anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tropicalforestryinstitute.org/ |title=Commemorating 75 Years |publisher=Fs.fed.us |date= |accessdate=2014-05-18}}</ref>

Its headquarters building was designed by architect [[W. Ellis Groben]].<ref name=annualletter>{{cite web|url=http://www.fs.fed.us/global/iitf/pubs/IITF_gtr31.pdf |title=US Forest Service Annual Letter 2002-2003, General Technical Report IITF-GTR-31 |date=December 2006}}</ref>

